# New Laptop Setup — Sweet Media Platform

**This rule exists to help the AI assistant onboard Ethan to a new machine.**
Once setup is complete, this file can be deleted.

---

## Context

Ethan switched to a new laptop. The full codebase is on GitHub. All secret env files were backed up to `~/Desktop/sweetmedia-env-backup.tar.gz` from the old machine and should be transferred to the new one.

---

## Step 1 — Install System Dependencies

Run these in order:

```bash
# Homebrew (if not installed)
/bin/bash -c "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/HEAD/install.sh)"

# Node version manager
brew install nvm
# Then follow the shell config instructions nvm prints (add to ~/.zshrc)
nvm install --lts
nvm use --lts

# pnpm — must match monorepo version
npm install -g pnpm@10.33.2

# Supabase CLI
brew install supabase/tap/supabase

# Vercel CLI
pnpm install -g vercel

# GitHub CLI
brew install gh
gh auth login
```

---

## Step 2 — Clone the Repo

```bash
git clone https://github.com/ethansweet35/sweet-media-platform.git
cd sweet-media-platform
```

---

## Step 3 — Restore Env Files

Copy `sweetmedia-env-backup.tar.gz` from the old machine (Desktop) to the new machine, then:

```bash
cd /path/to/sweet-media-platform
tar -xzf ~/Desktop/sweetmedia-env-backup.tar.gz
```

This restores:
- `.env` (root — all shared platform secrets)
- `apps/addiction-interventions/.env.local`
- `apps/cipher-billing/.env.local`
- `apps/inner-peak-colorado/.env.local`
- `apps/mountainview-treatment/.env.local`
- `apps/northbound-treatment/.env.local`
- `apps/rize-oc/.env.local`
- `apps/simple-health/.env.local`
- `apps/sweet-media/.env.local`
- `scripts/migrate-wp-media.mjs` (untracked script)
- `wp-media-migration-progress.json` (untracked migration progress)

If the tarball is not available, use `vercel env pull .env.local` inside each app directory as a fallback for the per-app files. The root `.env` would need to be rebuilt from 1Password.

---

## Step 4 — Install Dependencies

```bash
# From repo root
pnpm install
```

---

## Step 5 — Verify CLI Auth

```bash
# Supabase
supabase login
# (uses SUPABASE_ACCESS_TOKEN from .env — or login via browser)

# Vercel
vercel whoami
# (uses VERCEL_TOKEN from .env — or run: vercel login)

# GitHub
gh auth status
```

---

## Step 6 — Verify Dev Server

```bash
pnpm dev
# Should start all apps except client-template (filtered out by root turbo config)
```

---

## Root `.env` Keys Reference

The root `.env` (not committed to git) contains these keys — all should be restored from the tarball or 1Password:

- `SUPABASE_ACCESS_TOKEN` — Supabase management API / CLI auth
- `OPENROUTER_API_KEY` — Blog AI generation, Content Editor
- `OPENAI_API_KEY` — Image generation (DALL-E), blog fallback
- `GOOGLE_INDEXING_CLIENT_EMAIL` — Google Indexing API service account
- `GOOGLE_INDEXING_PRIVATE_KEY` — Google Indexing API private key
- `GOOGLE_NLP_API_KEY` — Content Editor entity extraction
- `GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID` / `GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_SECRET` — OAuth
- `DATAFORSEO_LOGIN` / `DATAFORSEO_PASSWORD` — SERP data for Content Editor
- `FIRECRAWL_API_KEY` — Competitor page scraping
- `SEMRUSH_API_KEY` — Keyword research
- `BLOG_WEBHOOK_SECRET` — blog-webhook Edge Function auth
- `VERCEL_TOKEN` — Vercel CLI / publish-client-to-vercel.mjs script
- `GITHUB_REPO` — used by setup scripts

---

## Per-App `.env.local` Keys Reference

Each app's `.env.local` contains:

**Public vars** (Supabase connection):
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL`
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY`
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY`
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_ID`
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL`

**Secret vars** (per-brand):
- `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY`
- `RESEND_API_KEY`
- `CONTACT_TO_EMAIL`, `CONTACT_FROM_EMAIL`, `CONTACT_BRAND_NAME`

**Shared platform secrets** (same values as root `.env`):
- `OPENROUTER_API_KEY`, `OPENAI_API_KEY`, `SEMRUSH_API_KEY`
- `DATAFORSEO_LOGIN`, `DATAFORSEO_PASSWORD`
- `FIRECRAWL_API_KEY`, `GOOGLE_NLP_API_KEY`

